---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "@id": "https://pakistanbill.online/blog/electricity-bill-calculator-guide/#article",
    "headline": "How to Calculate Your Pakistan Electricity Bill — Formula & Tool 2026",
    "description": "Learn the exact formula to calculate any Pakistan electricity bill manually. Full breakdown: tariff slabs, FPA, FC Surcharge, NJ Surcharge, GST, meter rent. Use our free calculator for instant results.",
    "url": "https://pakistanbill.online/blog/electricity-bill-calculator-guide/",
    "datePublished": "2026-01-15",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-11",
    "author": {"@type": "Organization", "name": "PakistanBill", "@id": "https://pakistanbill.online/#organization"},
    "publisher": {"@id": "https://pakistanbill.online/#organization"},
    "isPartOf": {"@id": "https://pakistanbill.online/#website"},
    "inLanguage": "en-PK"
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [{"@type":"Question","name":"How is Pakistan electricity bill calculated?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Pakistan electricity bill = Energy charges (per NEPRA slab rates) + FPA (Rs 0.48/unit) + FC Surcharge (Rs 0.43/unit) + NJ Surcharge (Rs 0.10/unit) + GST (17%) + Electricity Duty (1.5%) + TV Fee (Rs 35) + Meter Rent. Protected consumers use lower subsidized slab rates."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"What is the electricity bill formula for 300 units in Pakistan 2026?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For 300 units (Unprotected): Energy = (100×23.59) + (100×30.07) + (100×34.26) = Rs 8,792. Add FPA Rs 144 + FC Rs 129 + NJ Rs 30 + GST ~Rs 1,520 + Meter Rent ~Rs 1,000 = approximately Rs 11,700 total. Use our calculator for exact figures."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"What is FPA in electricity bill?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"FPA (Fuel Price Adjustment) is a monthly variable charge based on actual fuel costs. NEPRA determines it monthly. In March 2026 it is approximately Rs 0.48/unit, but it changes every month."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"Why is my electricity bill higher than calculation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Common reasons: (1) Estimated meter reading instead of actual — check if your bill says Estimated; (2) You crossed from Protected to Unprotected status; (3) TP (Theft Penalty) charge added; (4) Arrears from previous months; (5) MDI penalty (for commercial/industrial). Check each line item on your bill."}}]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://pakistanbill.online/"},
      {"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"Blog","item":"https://pakistanbill.online/blog/"},
      {"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"name":"How to Calculate Your Pakistan Electricity Bill — Formula & Tool 2026","item":"https://pakistanbill.online/blog/electricity-bill-calculator-guide/"}
    ]
  }
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="How to Calculate Pakistan Electricity Bill — Formula 2026"
  description="Exact formula to calculate Pakistan electricity bill: tariff slabs, FPA Rs 0.48, FC Surcharge, GST 17%. Step-by-step with worked example. Free calculator."
  canonical="/blog/electricity-bill-calculator-guide/"
  schema={schema}
  lastmod="2026-03-11"
  pageType="article"
>
  <div class="bg-neutral-100 border-b border-neutral-200">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-2">
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-neutral-500">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary-600">Home</a>
        <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-primary-600">Blog</a>
        <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        <span class="text-neutral-800 font-medium truncate">How to Calculate Your Pakistan Electricity Bill — Formula & Tool 2026</span>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-10">
    <div class="mb-6">
      <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 bg-primary-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Bill Guide</span>
      <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400 ml-3">Updated March 2026</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">How to Calculate Your Pakistan Electricity Bill — Complete Formula 2026</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 italic mb-2">Keywords: electricity bill calculator pakistan, how to calculate electricity bill, bijli bill calculation, unit rate calculation pakistan, lesco bill calculate, nepra tariff calculation</p>

    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      
    <p>Wondering why your electricity bill came out higher than expected? Understanding exactly <strong>how Pakistan electricity bills are calculated</strong> empowers you to verify every rupee. This guide explains the complete calculation formula used by all DISCOs — LESCO, MEPCO, GEPCO, FESCO, IESCO, and all others.</p>

    <div style="background:#fffbeb;border-left:4px solid #f59e0b;padding:1rem 1.5rem;border-radius:8px;margin:1.5rem 0;">
      <strong>Use our free calculator:</strong> Skip the manual math — <a href="/electricity-bill-calculator/" style="color:#01411C;font-weight:600;">use our Pakistan Electricity Bill Calculator →</a> for instant results with all 2026 rates pre-loaded.
    </div>

    
  <!-- Contextual Internal Links -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;border:1px solid #e2e8f0;border-radius:12px;padding:1.25rem;margin:1.5rem 0;">
    <p style="font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:700;color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.05em;margin-bottom:0.6rem;">Related Tools & Guides</p>
    <div><a href="https://pakistanbill.online/electricity-bill-calculator/" style="display:inline-block;background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:8px;padding:0.3rem 0.7rem;font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:600;color:#14532d;margin:0.2rem;text-decoration:none;">use our free calculator</a><a href="https://pakistanbill.online/dashboard/" style="display:inline-block;background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:8px;padding:0.3rem 0.7rem;font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:600;color:#14532d;margin:0.2rem;text-decoration:none;">check your bill now</a><a href="https://pakistanbill.online/blog/how-to-find-nepra-tariff-hike/" style="display:inline-block;background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:8px;padding:0.3rem 0.7rem;font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:600;color:#14532d;margin:0.2rem;text-decoration:none;">NEPRA tariff 2026</a><a href="https://pakistanbill.online/blog/fpa-charges-explained/" style="display:inline-block;background:#f0fdf4;border:1px solid #bbf7d0;border-radius:8px;padding:0.3rem 0.7rem;font-size:0.8rem;font-weight:600;color:#14532d;margin:0.2rem;text-decoration:none;">FPA charges explained</a></div>
  </section>
  <h2>The Complete Bill Calculation Formula</h2>
    <div style="background:#1e293b;color:#e2e8f0;padding:1.5rem;border-radius:12px;font-family:monospace;font-size:0.9rem;margin:1.5rem 0;line-height:2;">
      <div style="color:#86efac;">Total Bill =</div>
      <div style="margin-left:1.5rem;">Energy Charges (by slab)</div>
      <div style="margin-left:1.5rem;">+ FPA (Rs 0.48 × units)</div>
      <div style="margin-left:1.5rem;">+ FC Surcharge (Rs 0.43 × units)</div>
      <div style="margin-left:1.5rem;">+ NJ Surcharge (Rs 0.10 × units)</div>
      <div style="margin-left:1.5rem;">+ GST (17% on energy + FPA)</div>
      <div style="margin-left:1.5rem;">+ Electricity Duty (1.5%)</div>
      <div style="margin-left:1.5rem;">+ TV Fee (Rs 35 flat)</div>
      <div style="margin-left:1.5rem;">+ Meter Rent (~Rs 1,000+)</div>
    </div>

    <h2>Step-by-Step Example: 350 Units (Unprotected Consumer)</h2>

    <p><strong>Step 1: Energy Charges (Slab Calculation)</strong></p>
    <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:0.75rem 0;">
      <thead style="background:#374151;color:white;"><tr><th style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:left;">Slab</th><th style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;">Units</th><th style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;">Rate</th><th style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;">Amount</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><td style="padding:0.6rem;">1–100</td><td style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;">100</td><td style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;">Rs 23.59</td><td style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;font-weight:600;">Rs 2,359</td></tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><td style="padding:0.6rem;">101–200</td><td style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;">100</td><td style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;">Rs 30.07</td><td style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;font-weight:600;">Rs 3,007</td></tr>
        <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><td style="padding:0.6rem;">201–350</td><td style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;">150</td><td style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;">Rs 34.26</td><td style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;font-weight:600;">Rs 5,139</td></tr>
        <tr style="background:#f8f9fa;font-weight:700;"><td style="padding:0.6rem;">Energy Total</td><td style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;">350</td><td style="padding:0.6rem;"></td><td style="padding:0.6rem;text-align:right;">Rs 10,505</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p><strong>Step 2: Add Variable Surcharges</strong></p>
    <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:2.2;">
      <li>FPA: 350 × Rs 0.48 = <strong>Rs 168</strong></li>
      <li>FC Surcharge: 350 × Rs 0.43 = <strong>Rs 150.50</strong></li>
      <li>NJ Surcharge: 350 × Rs 0.10 = <strong>Rs 35</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Step 3: Add Taxes</strong></p>
    <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:2.2;">
      <li>GST (17%): (10,505 + 168) × 17% = <strong>Rs 1,814</strong></li>
      <li>Electricity Duty (1.5%): 10,505 × 1.5% = <strong>Rs 158</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Step 4: Fixed Charges</strong></p>
    <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:2.2;">
      <li>TV Fee: <strong>Rs 35</strong></li>
      <li>Meter Rent: <strong>~Rs 1,000</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Total Estimated Bill: ~Rs 13,865</strong></p>

    <p>For an instant, accurate calculation at current 2026 rates, use our <a href="/electricity-bill-calculator/"><strong>free electricity bill calculator →</strong></a></p>

    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-10">
      {[{ q: `How is Pakistan electricity bill calculated?`, a: `Pakistan electricity bill = Energy charges (per NEPRA slab rates) + FPA (Rs 0.48/unit) + FC Surcharge (Rs 0.43/unit) + NJ Surcharge (Rs 0.10/unit) + GST (17%) + Electricity Duty (1.5%) + TV Fee (Rs 35) + Meter Rent. Protected consumers use lower subsidized slab rates.` },
        { q: `What is the electricity bill formula for 300 units in Pakistan 2026?`, a: `For 300 units (Unprotected): Energy = (100×23.59) + (100×30.07) + (100×34.26) = Rs 8,792. Add FPA Rs 144 + FC Rs 129 + NJ Rs 30 + GST ~Rs 1,520 + Meter Rent ~Rs 1,000 = approximately Rs 11,700 total. Use our calculator for exact figures.` },
        { q: `What is FPA in electricity bill?`, a: `FPA (Fuel Price Adjustment) is a monthly variable charge based on actual fuel costs. NEPRA determines it monthly. In March 2026 it is approximately Rs 0.48/unit, but it changes every month.` },
        { q: `Why is my electricity bill higher than calculation?`, a: `Common reasons: (1) Estimated meter reading instead of actual — check if your bill says Estimated; (2) You crossed from Protected to Unprotected status; (3) TP (Theft Penalty) charge added; (4) Arrears from previous months; (5) MDI penalty (for commercial/industrial). Check each line item on your bill.` }].map((faq) => (
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-question">{faq.q}</summary>
          <div class="px-4 pb-4 text-sm text-neutral-600">{faq.a}</div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- Related bill checkers -->
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-2xl p-5 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-primary-800 mb-3">Check Your Bill Right Now</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        {"LESCO,MEPCO,GEPCO,FESCO,IESCO,PESCO,K-Electric,SNGPL,PTCL".split(",").map(n => (
          <a href={`/${n.toLowerCase().replace("k-electric","k-electric-bill").replace("sngpl","sngpl-bill").replace("ptcl","ptcl-bill").replace(/^([a-z]+)$/, "$1-bill")}/`}
             class="text-sm font-semibold bg-white border border-primary-200 rounded-lg px-3 py-1.5 text-primary-700 hover:bg-primary-100 transition-colors">
            {n} →
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Related blog posts -->
    <div class="border-t border-neutral-200 pt-6">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-4">More Electricity Bill Guides</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        {[
          ["How to Read Your Electricity Bill","/blog/how-to-read-electricity-bill/"],
          ["FPA Charges Explained","/blog/fpa-charges-explained/"],
          ["Electricity Tariff 2026","/blog/electricity-tariff-2026/"],
          ["Peak Hours — All DISCOs","/blog/peak-hours-all-discos/"],
          ["How to Pay Bill Online","/blog/how-to-pay-online/"],
          ["How to Find Reference Number","/blog/how-to-find-reference-number/"],
          ["Bill Calculator Guide","/blog/electricity-bill-calculator-guide/"],
          ["NEPRA Tariff Hike 2026","/blog/how-to-find-nepra-tariff-hike/"],
        ].map((item) => (
          <a href={item[1]} class="text-sm text-primary-600 hover:underline bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg px-3 py-2">→ {item[0]}</a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

<p>Use PakistanBill.online's <a href="/electricity-bill-calculator/"><strong>free electricity bill calculator</strong></a> to compute your exact bill instantly. We are <strong>Pakistan's only platform</strong> covering all 19 utility providers — so after calculating, you can also check your real bill: <a href="/lesco-bill/">LESCO</a> | <a href="/mepco-bill/">MEPCO</a> | <a href="/gepco-bill/">GEPCO</a> | <a href="/fesco-bill/">FESCO</a> | <a href="/iesco-bill/">IESCO</a> | <a href="/k-electric-bill/">K-Electric</a>. Or open the <a href="/dashboard/">universal bill dashboard</a> to check any provider without switching pages.</p>
</BaseLayout>
